places.name: Mueller Lake Park
places.description: It's a nice quick walk, there are ice cream shop and bars, Ramen restaurant near by. They have farmers market every Sunday.

places.name: Texas Capitol
places.description: It may be a cliché, but I would like everyone to visit the Texas Capitol at least once. It may be similar to Tokyo Tower for people in Tokyo, but it is taller than the White House and the interior is also wonderful, so I recommend it.

places.name: Bob Bullock History Museum
places.description: Exhibits, IMAX films & educational experiences aim to tell & interpret the story of Texas.

places.name: Laguna Gloria
places.description: Contemporary art museum featuring rotating, innovative exhibits & offering educational programs.

places.name: The Driskill
places.description: Dating from 1886, this opulent Downtown hotel is within a 12-minute walk of the Texas State Capitol and the Austin Convention Center.

places.name: Mt Bonnell
places.description: 5.1-acre park known for its elevated summit offering sweeping views of Lake Austin.

places.name: Lady Bird Johnson Wildflower Center
places.description: Center focused on native Texas plants & their benefits, founded by & named for a former first lady.

places.name: The Oasis On Lake Travis
places.description: Nachos, salads & margaritas on tiered outdoor decks overlooking Lake Travis.

places.name: Zilker Botanical Gardens
places.description: 31-acre garden in Zilker Park with plants, ponds & trails, plus educational programs for kids.

places.name: Cathedral of Junk
places.description: This whimsical, multilevel shelter is made with 60+ tons of used furniture, home goods & other junk.

places.name: Barton Springs
places.description: The pool itself measures three acres in size, and is fed from underground springs with an average temperature of 68-70 degrees, ideal for year-round swimming.

places.name: Barton Creek Greenbelt
places.description: This popular urban natural area offers opportunities for biking, hiking, swimming & rock climbing.

places.name: The Long Center for the Performing Arts
places.description: A stunning complex with a diverse line-up of local & national artists, plus free community events.

places.name: Ummlauf Sculpture Garden + Museum
places.description: Exhibition of Charles Umlauf's works with an outdoor collection of touchable bronze sculptures.

places.name: Zilker Metropolitan Park
places.description: 351-acre, urban park with botanical gardens, a spring-fed pool, a theater & sports facilities.

places.name: Enchanted Rock
places.description: Popular for hiking & scenic views, this landmark pink granite rock is shaped like a dome.

places.name: Pedernales Falls State Park
places.description: 5,200-acre park with hiking & horseback riding trails, campsites, river swimming & scenic vistas.

places.name: Lost Maples State Natural Area
places.description: Birds & wildlife, plus limestone canyons, plateaus & fall foliage along a river valley.

places.name: Botanical Gates of Paradise
places.description: Attraction inside the Zilker Botanical Garden.

places.name: Loro Asian Smokhouse & Bar
places.description: This is a collaboration between the famous Texas BBQ restaurant Franklin Barbecue and Japanese restaurant Uchi, and they sometimes serve ramen.

places.name: Mozart's Coffee Roasters
places.description: Beans flame-roasted on-site, plus bakery goods, frequent live music & patio seating on Lake Austin. They hold a wonderful light-up event in the winter.

places.name: Fonda San Miguel
places.description: Sophisticated takes on traditional Mexican cuisine served in a colorful, hacienda-style space.

places.name: Hopfields
places.description: This gastropub offers a broad craft beer selection & French-inspired fare in a rustic-chic setting.

places.name: Terry Black's Barbecue
places.description: Spacious, casual stop for pit-smoked meats & housemade sides from famous 4th-generation pitmasters.

places.name: Swedish Hill
places.description: Longtime bakery with a cozy ambiance & outdoor seating selling baked goods, breads & lunch fare.

places.name: Domo Alley-Gato Tatsu-Ya
places.description: Dog-friendly stop with late hours & outdoor seating focusing on creative highballs & Japanese curry.

places.name: Fukumoto
places.description: Japanese izakaya serving skewers, sushi & cooked seafood imported from Japan in a lofty, hip space.

places.name: Saltgrass Steak House
places.description: Informal Texas-themed chain offers a meaty menu & full bar amid cattle kitsch decor.

places.name: Kyoko Coffee
places.description: Kyoko Coffee is a Japanese-inspired, kawaii-themed coffee shop rooted in omotenashi—the Japanese philosophy of wholehearted hospitality.

places.name: Miyo Yakitori & Sushi
places.description: Serving traditional Japanese cuisine along with our Yakitori and Sushi. Udon, Tonkatsu , Bento, and Ramen, are a few example of the cuisines we serve.

places.name: KANE
places.description: Asian-owned sushi restaurant.

places.name: Don Don Express
places.description: Asian-owned family-style restaurant.

places.name: Kanji Ramen
places.description: Noodles & small plates are served at this snug shop featuring veggie options & colorful wall art.

places.name: 85°C Bakery Cafe
places.description: Bakery/cafe chain with roots in Taiwan, offering coffee & tea plus international desserts & breads.

places.name: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
places.description: An array of sushi and other Japanese dishes rotates to diners' booths on a conveyor belt.

places.name: Matsuba Ramen
places.description: Matsuba is here to satisfy your cravings with rich, flavorful paitan ramen, made with a chicken broth that takes 20 hours of love and care that'll warm your soul (and your belly).

places.name: Soto
places.description: Upscale Japanese restaurant that serves sushi, cocktails & more amid a sleek, grey & black space.

places.name: 888 Pan Asian Restaurant
places.description: A menu true to its namesake with all things Asian from pho to pad thai, plus a buffet.

places.name: Bamboo Garden Wok 'N' Grill
places.description: Chinese restaurant.

places.name: Komé: Sushi Kitchen
places.description: Trendy sushi joint with homestyle Japanese plates in a stylish, bamboo-accented space.

places.name: Uchi Austin
places.description: Sushi plus creative hot & cold dishes from chef Tyson Cole in a stylish, sophisticated setting.

places.name: Uchiko Austin
places.description: Offshoot of the famed Uchi restaurant with upscale sushi & small plates in a farmhouse-chic space.

places.name: The Salt Lick BBQ
places.description: Venerable outpost serving Texas-style BBQ with famous sauces & rubs in a relaxed, rustic setting.
